org.openhab.binding.velux.internal.bridge.slip

Class SCrunProductCommand

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openhab.binding.velux.internal.bridge.common.RunProductCommand
      • org.openhab.binding.velux.internal.bridge.slip.SCrunProductCommand
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    BridgeCommunicationProtocol, SlipBridgeCommunicationProtocol

    @NonNullByDefault
class SCrunProductCommand
extends RunProductCommand
implements SlipBridgeCommunicationProtocol
    Protocol specific bridge communication supported by the Velux bridge: Send Command to Actuator

    Common Message semantic: Communication with the bridge and (optionally) storing returned information within the class itself.

    As 3rd level class it defines informations how to send query and receive answer through the VeluxBridgeProvider as described by the interface SlipBridgeCommunicationProtocol.

    Methods in addition to the mentioned interface:

    • setNodeAndMainParameter(int, int) to define the node and intended parameter value.
    Author:
    Guenther Schreiner - Initial contribution.
    See Also:
    RunProductCommand, SlipBridgeCommunicationProtocol
